# Step 8: Allow Only Selected Sites for LAN Client

Create chain:

```bash
iptables -N CDAC
```

Redirect LAN traffic:

```bash
iptables -I FORWARD 1 \
-s 192.168.25.0/24 \
-j CDAC
```

---

Allow DNS:

```bash
iptables -A CDAC \
-d 192.168.72.20 \
-p udp --dport 53 \
-j ACCEPT
```

---

Resolve IPs:

```bash
host google.com
host microsoft.com
host cdac.in
```

Suppose you get IPs.

Allow:

```bash
iptables -A CDAC -d <google-ip> -j ACCEPT
iptables -A CDAC -d <microsoft-ip> -j ACCEPT
iptables -A CDAC -d <cdac-ip> -j ACCEPT
```

---

Drop everything else:

```bash
iptables -A CDAC -j DROP
```

---

# Effect

LAN Client:

✅ Google

✅ Microsoft

✅ CDAC

✅ DNS

❌ Everything Else

