# Step 9: Allow Full Access to DMZ Client

DMZ requirement:

> Allow full traffic to DMZ client

Rule:

```bash
iptables -A FORWARD \
-s 192.168.35.0/24 \
-j ACCEPT
```

---

# Step 10: Configure Port Forwarding

Assignment requirement:

> Website on DMZ should be accessible using Firewall WAN IP

This is DNAT.

---

Find WAN IP:

```bash
ip -br a
```

Example:

```text
192.168.1.12
```

---

Create Port Forward:

```bash
iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING \
-p tcp \
--dport 80 \
-j DNAT \
--to-destination 192.168.35.10:80
```

---

Allow Forwarding:

```bash
iptables -A FORWARD \
-p tcp \
-d 192.168.35.10 \
--dport 80 \
-j ACCEPT
```

---

